OTTAWA , August 17 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Canada is imposing a ban on blood donation by those visiting Britain for six months or more between 1980 and 1996 .
Health Canada said Tuesday that the ban , which takes effect on February 17 , 2000 , is intended to reduce possibility of transmitting `` mad cow '' disease by means of blood transfusion .
Health Canada decided on the ban following months of consultations with the Canadian Blood Serives and Hema - Quebec , which is also an operator of the national blood service , the federal department said .
